parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electro-hydraulic power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering fails or becomes difficult to operate
the steering wheel seizes or becomes hard to turn
the power steering pump makes a loud noise
the power steering fluid leaks or overheats
the vehicle's airbag warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbags not deploying in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
and the airbags may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and failure of the windshield can cause a loss of visibility, leading to accidents, and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The windshield develops cracks or shatters without any apparent reason
often starting from the edges or corners of the windshield; cracks may appear suddenly
even when the vehicle is stationary; windshield may creak or make noise while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic window motor can cause the window to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The window does not move when the switch is activated; the window motor makes unusual noises or vibrations; the window becomes stuck in an open or closed position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, especially in rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not move or move erratically; the windshield wiper motor makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior door latch mechanism can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The door does not open or close properly; the door latch mechanism makes unusual noises or vibrations.
